Sep 23, 2013
Lisa Nelms

        rated it
        it was amazing



I think David Anderson is a 21st century C.S. Lewis. His book speaks to anyone who has suffered a loss, and let's face it, that's everyone. I am buying a copy for everyone I love and care about, especially friends my age. I am a baby boomer and many of us are facing lots of changes - empty nests, parents dying, health failing us, feeling unappreciated in the work place etc... It's a pithy read. I recommend reading it when there are no distractions and I especially recommend discussing it with a
I think David Anderson is a 21st century C.S. Lewis. His book speaks to anyone who has suffered a loss, and let's face it, that's everyone. I am buying a copy for everyone I love and care about, especially friends my age. I am a baby boomer and many of us are facing lots of changes - empty nests, parents dying, health failing us, feeling unappreciated in the work place etc... It's a pithy read. I recommend reading it when there are no distractions and I especially recommend discussing it with a friend experiencing a similar loss. It could be very therapeutic.
