Really good book for when you suddenly find that your beliefs that you had don't seem to work for you anymore, however that realisation comes about. Need to be careful where you are in such a journey when you read it, I have just read it in August 2014, at a point when my faith, to me, felt truly useless, consequently I romped through the first half of the book in 2 days, but took a week to read the rest, which I found a bit heavy going, but that is more about where I am, as opposed to what he w
Really good book for when you suddenly find that your beliefs that you had don't seem to work for you anymore, however that realisation comes about. Need to be careful where you are in such a journey when you read it, I have just read it in August 2014, at a point when my faith, to me, felt truly useless, consequently I romped through the first half of the book in 2 days, but took a week to read the rest, which I found a bit heavy going, but that is more about where I am, as opposed to what he was saying.However, it was all very practical, engaging and routed in a reality I truly recognised. He quotes Richard Rohr's "Falling Upwards" a fair bit, so am going to read that next.."
