There was a problem loading comments right now. Please try again later.5.0 out of 5 starsFull circle.ByJenon November 2, 2013Format: Kindle Edition|Verified PurchaseDid your religious upbringing require you to check your brain at the door because it required belief in every word of the Bible, because it made you feel that you were such an awful sinner you weren't good enough for God, or because it excluded entire classes of people from salvation?  Did that upbringing lead you to drop your faith entirely, but you now feel a spiritual hunger?  Then "Losing Your Faith, Finding Your Soul" is the book for you.  David Anderson leads you on a journey where you must stand apart from your family of origin in order to hear God speak to your own heart.  The journey continues as you learn to forgive.  The chapter on forgiveness gave me some new ways of thinking about the topic, especially Anderson's ideas on not taking offense to begin with.  In the end, you come back to those flawed people from your past -- and perhaps even the religious tradition you left -- with renewed faith and understanding, able to love them and yourself through God's grace.  Anderson takes you on this full circle journey with a beautiful command of language and many engaging stories from his own life and work as an Episcopal priest.  I felt renewed in spirit after reading this book, able to recognize parts of the journey I've completed, and with a road map for my travels ahead.0Comment|
